The paper deals with compressive sensing and signal recovery, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on 2D signals, which are often encountered in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The proposed algorithm is based on thresholding, which is a common technique in sparse signal processing (cs.SI).
